  {
    "Id": "780424",
    "ThreadId": "327751",
    "Html": "<p>Hi,</p>\r\n<p>This is very simple. Get a reference to your VM in the code behind:</p>\r\n<p>public MyViewModel Vm<br />{<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; get<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; {<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; return (MyViewModel)DataContext;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; }<br />}&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>then, in the Page's constructor, after the call to InitializeComponent, add an event handler to Vm.PropertyChanged.</p>\r\n<p>Hope this helps,</p>\r\n<p>Laurent</p>",
    "PostedDate": "2012-02-19T10:01:40.307-08:00",
    "UserRole": null,
    "MarkedAsAnswerDate": null
  },
